The AddFlight class represents a command to add a new flight to the Flight Booking System.

The `Booking` class represents a reservation made by a customer for a specific flight.

The BookingDataManager class manages the loading and storing of booking data for the Flight Booking System from/to a text file.

The CancelBookingPanel class represents a modal dialog for canceling a booking in the Flight Booking System.

The Command interface defines the contract for all commands in the Flight Booking System application.

The CommandParser class parses user input to create appropriate Command objects.

The `Customer` class represents a customer of the flight booking system.

Manages the loading and storing of customer data for the Flight Booking System from/to a text file.

The DataManager interface defines methods to load and store data for the Flight Booking System.

Enum representing different classes of a flight.

The FlightBookingSystemData class manages the loading and storing of data for the Flight Booking System.

FlightBookingSystemException extends Exception class and is a custom exception that is used to notify the user about errors or invalid commands within the flight booking system.

The FlightDataManager class implements DataManager to manage loading and storing Flight data for the Flight Booking System.
